The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 1: The consortium of Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd (BPCL) and Videocon Industries has discovered a hydrocarbon field in offshore Brazil. The hydrocarbon discovery was made by Anadarko Petroleum Corporation, the operator of block BM-C-30, in which the Videocon and BPCL combine hold a 25 per cent stake.                            
	 Mumbai, Oct. 1: Gremach Infrastructure Equipments amp; Projects, which has found coking coal in its mines in Mozambique, plans to raise $50 million by diluting its stake in the company.                            
	 Mumbai, Oct. 1: All commodity markets, including the Bombay Stock Exchange, National Stock Exchange, forex and the money market will remain closed on October 2 because of Gandhi Jayanti and Id. The bullion market will, however, remain open.                            
	 Paris, Oct. 1: The country will certainly look at removing the FDI cap of 51 per cent in single-brand retail if the situation demands, commerce minister Kamal Nath said.                            
	 Mumbai, Oct. 1: Hindalco Industries rights offer is likely to sail through as the issue has received commitment from merchant bankers and financial institutions and the GDR entitlement has been fully subscribed.                                                                                                                         
